{"lemma":"بُرْنُسٌ","slug":"بُرْنُسٌ","root":"ب.ر.ن.س","root_slug":"ب-ر-ن-س","root_link":"/words/roots/ب-ر-ن-س","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n2399"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A8%D9%8F%D8%B1%D9%92%D9%86%D9%8F%D8%B3%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"calotte","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"burnoose, cloak"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to dress in a burnoose","tags":["transitive"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Via some Aramaic form (compare Mishnaic Hebrew בירוס, Classical Syriac ܒܝܪܘܢܐ) from Byzantine Greek βίρρος (bírros), from Latin birrus, from Gaulish, from Proto-Celtic *birros (“short”). Doublet of بِرْنِيطَة (birnīṭa).\n\nDenominal verb of بُرْنُس (burnus)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n2399","headword_ar":"بُرْنُسٌ","root":"brns","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A long"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qalanosuwap","text_ar":"قَلَنْسُوَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which the devotees used to wear in the first age of ElIslám:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any garment of which the head forms a part,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being joined to it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whether it be a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dur~aAEap","text_ar":"دُرَّاعَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mimoTar","text_ar":"مِمْطَر"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jub~ap","text_ar":"جُبَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, K;) and this is said to be the correct explanation: (TA:) [agreeably with the latter explanation, it is applied in the present day to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a hooded cloak,"},{"kind":"text","text":"mostly"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of white woollen stuff;"},{"kind":"text","text":"but often,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of cloth of any colour:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baraAnisu","text_ar":"بَرَانِسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) [some say] it is from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Albirosu","text_ar":"البِرْسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning “cotton,” and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"n","text_ar":"ن"},{"kind":"text","text":"is augmentative: or, accord. to some, it is not Arabic. (TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buronusu AlHusoni","text_ar":"بُرْنُسُ الحُسْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Comely,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goodly, hair."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mlA^","text_ar":"ملا"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","M","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}